Easiest Salmon Bowl! We’ve been making this weekly and it’s so refreshing + a good quick/easy dinner. Recipe below! 

SALMON BOWLS: 
+ Cut salmon into bite size squares (we take the skin off for this)
+ Marinate in 2TBSP each of hot honey, soy sauce & olive oil 
+ Add panko breadcrumbs to a bowl with salt, pepper, garlic powder, Parmesan and smoked paprika. Mix!
+ Coat Salmon bites into breadcrumb mixed and evenly spread onto airfryer pan
+ Air fry salmon at 400 for 8 minutes 

+ Dice up the following veggies (or whatever you prefer!) 
•tomato’s, onion, jalapeños, mango, avocado + cilantro
+ Add rice to your bowl/plate, drizzle with soy sauce 
+ Add cooked salmon + veggies to bowl, drizzle hot honey onto salmon and add cilantro
+ Serve and enjoy!!!! 💚 

I got this recipe from @paigeejenna & love her!! 🫶🏼🫶🏼 #salmonbowls #salmonbowl #summermeals #summerbowls #salmonbowlrecipe #recipes #summerrecipes
